# Tailwind CSS Exclusivity

To maintain a consistent design system and keep things simple for non-technical vibe coders, we strictly use Tailwind CSS utility classes.

- **No Custom CSS:** Do not write custom CSS in `.css` files or use `<style>` blocks.
- **No Inline Styles:** Do not use the `style="..."` attribute unless it is strictly necessary for dynamic Javascript-calculated values (like a chart progress bar width).

```html
<!-- ❌ BAD: Using inline styles -->
<div style="background-color: red; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px;">
  Warning
</div>

<!-- ✅ GOOD: Using Tailwind utility classes -->
<div class="bg-red-500 p-4 rounded-md">
  Warning
</div>
```

```javascript
// ❌ BAD: Applying styles directly via JS
element.style.marginTop = '20px';
element.style.color = '#333';

// ✅ GOOD: Toggling Tailwind classes via JS
element.classList.add('mt-5', 'text-gray-800');
```
